<paragraph blockId="1.[264,1324,1588,1894]" lastBlockId="2.[264,1323,284,470]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">
Antennae much longer than the combined length of head and pronotum. Integument highly setose. Setae on pronotum, sternum, abdomen and femora long. Median carina of pronotum distinct and slightly raised, but not constricted. Sulci distinct, but not deep. Sculpting pattern of dorsal surface of prozona papillulate. Lateral lobes of prozona slightly wrinkled. 
<collectingCountry box="[389,448,1828,1854]" name="India" pageId="1" pageNumber="44">Hind</collectingCountry>
angle of pronotum slightly obtuse­angular. Small granules present on pronotum and thorax. Anterior and posterior portion of pronotum similar width. Tegmina slightly extending beyond the tip of abdomen. Cerci quadrate, with length twice longer than width (
<figureCitation box="[406,473,324,350]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1636,1660]" captionTargetBox="[279,1307,542,1625]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,529,1627]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Schistocerca cohni n. sp. holotype dorsal view (A), holotype lateral view (B), “ basal eminence ” of zygoma (C), ectophallic sclerite (D), cingulum (E), epiphallus (F), endophallus (G), male epiproct (H), male subgenital plate (I), and male cercus (J)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172139/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[461,473,324,350]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
J). Apical tip of cercus slightly bilobed, with lower part extruding more than upper. Furcula small and rectangular. Epiproct with a pair of tubercle absent (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1636,1660]" captionTargetBox="[279,1307,542,1625]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,529,1627]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Schistocerca cohni n. sp. holotype dorsal view (A), holotype lateral view (B), “ basal eminence ” of zygoma (C), ectophallic sclerite (D), cingulum (E), epiphallus (F), endophallus (G), male epiproct (H), male subgenital plate (I), and male cercus (J)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172139/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<number box="[264,275,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
H). Subgenital plate with round apex (
<figureCitation box="[737,805,404,430]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[264,367,1636,1660]" captionTargetBox="[279,1307,542,1625]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[264,1323,529,1627]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Schistocerca cohni n. sp. holotype dorsal view (A), holotype lateral view (B), “ basal eminence ” of zygoma (C), ectophallic sclerite (D), cingulum (E), epiphallus (F), endophallus (G), male epiproct (H), male subgenital plate (I), and male cercus (J)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172139/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
Fig. 
<date box="[793,805,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
<number box="[793,805,404,430]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" value="1.0">1</number>
</date>
</figureCitation>
I). Apical lobes of subgenital plate not outwardly flared, with U­shaped notch.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/172139/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="45" targetBox="[279,1307,542,1625]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[264,1323,1636,1729]" pageId="2" pageNumber="45">
